## USER RESEARCH

**Top 5 Pain Points:**

1. **"Is the classic white french tip over?"** — Dominant anxiety in comment sections and PAA boxes; readers torn between the timeless classic and feeling dated. Multiple nail artists quoted explicitly saying thick white is "out" in 2026.
2. **"I can't get a straight smile line at home"** — Consistent DIY frustration across TikTok comments and nail forums; liner brush technique and nail guides repeatedly raised as solutions.
3. **"Which pastel colour actually looks good on my skin tone?"** — Colour indecision is a major pain point; readers want skin-tone guidance, not just a dump of shades.
4. **"Chrome tips look hard to do — is it a salon-only thing?"** — Chrome powder fear is real; users unsure if the DIY version looks as good. High search intent around "chrome nails at home."
5. **"I have short nails — do french tips even work on them?"** — Short nail concern appears persistently in micro french and coloured french tip content. Short almond + sqoval repeatedly cited as the answer.

**User Sentiment:** Aspirational but slightly anxious — readers want to feel current without being a slave to trend, and they're specifically worried about getting it wrong (dated vs modern, wearable vs costume-y).

